Text.Value: Nothing befitting a child. Nothing befitting any of our world's creatures.
You may be right. We've let a snake replace our leader. And the result... By the Treefather, that girl...
Please, do whatever you must to get him home. The grove needs him.
I found Halsin in the goblin camp, but he didn't survive.
I wish I could offer more assistance. For now, I must keep a close watch on Kagha.
And if I hadn't spoken up? What would have happened?
I hope to see both you and Halsin again soon.
Kagha seems happy to rule the roost. Who's your real leader?
Master Halsin. Perhaps goblin-caught, perhaps dead. He'd set... Mistress Kagha back in line. Hold her to task. Stop this damned ritual.
If only justice soothed my heart. A grove drenched in blood is no sanctuary at all.
...I apologise. I must have some time to myself.
We've let a snake replace our leader. She will see the tieflings driven out, or worse.
She is First Druid in Halsin's absence. With him caught - or dead - by goblins, none may gainsay her.
I'd like a more solid offer than 'anything'.
You have saved Kagha from herself. I cannot thank you enough.
I'll take my chances on Nettie.
The child is to blame. She shouldn't have stolen in the first place.
If no one's looking for Halsin, I could do it.
How did Kagha take over the whole grove?
Mercy on us, Silvanus - mercy, mercy, mercy.
Halsin is an elf with the presence of a bear. He left west, with the adventurers.
Leave.
More will die if the rite is finished. So many more, sent into a world gone mad...
The girl's parents will want vengeance.
May he rest in Summeroak forever. I...
We let this happen. We let this snake replace our leader.
Would you? I would give anything to see Halsin return home.
It was a terrible accident.
Never mind. I'm not interested.
That Kagha seems dangerous.
Perhaps his eyes are on Master Halsin now.
Yet for her to die like this, under the Treefather's gaze... perhaps it is justice.
By every star, by every vein on every leaf, she must.
The adventurers say they lost track of him in a temple to the west.
Should you change your mind, head west. Halsin is an elf with the presence of a bear.
You don't deserve the Treefather's mercy - you failed him. Failed your duty.
You let Kagha befoul this sacred place with a child's blood, yet you plead 'mercy'? Coward.
I hope to see Halsin return so he can help us heal.
We need Master Halsin. Without him, Kagha's ritual will divide this grove forever.
A child is dead. You don't deserve mercy.
That girl's parents want vengeance - and they deserve it.
That snake must be held accountable.
Ah, I see. You will find her deeper in the caves.
I pray the Treefather nourishes Kagha's wounded soul, now that she is dead.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: Kagha Turned good but died in the fight against the shadow druids

Text.Value: I pray she can heal what ails you.
I'm in need of a healer. Badly.
Like many, you seek Halsin's craft. But you'll have to settle for Nettie.
This is how a terrible cycle begins. All is out of balance.
You did well to speak up for the girl. That snake is fickle. A tragedy prevented.

EditorData.NodeContext: Grateful for the player's help, irritated at the 'snake' (Kagha)

Text.Value: Well seen. Well spotted. We've let a snake replace our leader.
Find her further in the cave. Her gift is great, too - you can trust her.

EditorData.InternalNodeContext: show this only if the player didn't already find Halsin, no need to be redundant if the player already knows
EditorData.logicalname: Only if player doesn't know about Halsin

Text.Value: But more will die if her ritual is finished. I doubt those exiled by the rite will survive long outside.
Your dismissal is no shield. Kagha will ensure all outsiders are driven from the grove.
No need to fret. I'll find him.
I'm looking for Nettie.
This has only happened because our true leader was taken from us.
Until Master Halsin returns, my eyes must stay on Kagha.
It is what Kagha desires. I doubt it is what Silvanus wants.
Preventable. The sickening result of sickening beliefs.
One meant to seal us in. Meant to seal them out. Blasphemous. The Treefather must see what's happening in his holy grove.
Our need is great. I will open the treasures of this grove to you, even if the circle forbids it.
Sounds like Halsin might be the better bet. Where is he?
My oath often aligns with the Treefather's will. He would not abide child-slaughter.
I swore an oath to stop terrible deeds like that. Monsters like her.
Please, if you find him, let me know.
To think Kagha had turned to the ways of shadow. Her corruption ran so deep.
I've heard there's some sort of ritual going on.
Would that I could track himself myself. But I cannot leave with Kagha doing as she wills.
Silvanus' blessing upon you. And my gratitude as well.
You won't mistake the First Druid for anyone else.
Sounds like I'd better leave.
I found Halsin in the goblin camp, but he can't return yet.

Synopsis: Rath is a human druid opposed to Kagha, who has taken control of the grove in Halsin's absence. He is a kind, determined man, who seeks to keep nature in balance and prevent violence at all costs.
